H.B. 660
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
Apr 1, 2025
SESSION 2025
HOUSE PRINCIPAL CLERK
H D
HOUSE BILL DRH40384-LGa-154
Short Title: Funds for Various Projects in Cabarrus Co. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative Echevarria.
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO APPROPRIATE FUNDS FOR VARIOUS PROJECTS IN THE TOWNS OF
3 MIDLAND AND HARRISBURG.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Office of State
6 Budget and Management the sum of seven million dollars ($7,000,000) in nonrecurring funds
7 for the 2025-2026 fiscal year to provide a directed grant to the Town of Midland for various road
8 improvements in the Bethel Glen Development and the Tucker Chase Development.
9 SECTION 2. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Office of State
10 Budget and Management the sum of twelve million seven hundred thousand dollars
11 ($12,700,000) in nonrecurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal year to provide a directed grant to
12 the Town of Harrisburg to be used as follows:
13 (1) Two million five hundred thousand dollars ($2,500,000) for turf fields.
14 (2) Nine million two hundred thousand dollars ($9,200,000) for the Harrisburg
15 passenger rail station.
16 (3) One million dollars ($1,000,000) to complete the Harrisburg YMCA building.
17 SECTION 3. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Office of State
18 Budget and Management the sum of one million nine hundred fifty thousand dollars ($1,950,000)
19 in nonrecurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal year to provide a directed grant to Cabarrus
20 County to be used for Cabarrus Rowan Community Health Center to expand and sustain access
21 to care in the County.
22 SECTION 4. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Office of State
23 Budget and Management the sum of one million dollars ($1,000,000) in nonrecurring funds for
24 the 2025-2026 fiscal year to provide a directed grant to Cabarrus Cooperative Christian Ministry,
25 Inc., a nonprofit organization, to assist members of the community experiencing crisis in the
26 areas of food, housing, or finances.
27 SECTION 5. This act becomes effective July 1, 2025.
*DRH40384-LGa-154*

